Simple and elegant is the best way to create a menu and recipes like this one are a shining example as to why that is. This egg focused dish is a stellar addition to any appetizer/salad selection and is very straight forward on prep. Have your eggs cooked and breaded, blanched and cooled asparagus ready, and make sure to have plenty of asparagus coulis for service. Herbs, flaky salt, and olive oil to finish… Order up!! 📝

These cured coho salmon “tarts” were inspired by @chefthomaskeller and his famous “Salmon Cornets” from The French Laundry. This dish is a creamy salmon tartare loaded with zesty lemon oil and a generous amount of fine herbs… all packed between two crispy (slightly sweet) tuiles that have a perfect kick of black pepper to finish. Perfect for weddings and grand events or just a fun Sunday champagne brunch. Video coming soon!!

#ad @nstomatoes are always in our fridge throughout the year and there’s a million and one ways to have fun with them in the kitchen. Most of the time we just run through them with a little salt or a simple balsamic vin, but today it’s a wood-fired flatbread with garden pesto marinated Cherubs/Constellation and ricotta cheese…super delish and simple to say the least. Any of the leftover marinated tomatoes end up on my morning breakfast bagel and it’s just the best wake me up bagel ever! #GoNatureSweet

Be sure to check out the link in my profile to have a chance at a summer getaway with @nstomatoes! Happy SUMMER ALL!! 

Ingredients:
-Pizza Dough
1 1/2 cups bread flour (ap works too)
1 cup warm water 
1 tbsp dry active yeast
2 tbsp brown sugar 
2 tbsp olive oil
1 tsp salt 

Pesto:
2 cups picked herbs (basil, chervil, fennel tops, parsley etc..)
1 cup olive oil 
1/4 cup almonds, pine nuts, or walnuts 
Salt and pepper to taste 

1 cup @nstomatoes Cherub/Constellation variety 
1/2 cup ricotta cheese

Watermelon season is in full swing here in middle Tennessee and we couldn’t be any happier with how they turned out our first year! Our very own front yard garden is pumping these beauties out and we are having an absolute blast picking the perfect one for the day, slicing it up, shoving our faces with as much as we can eat, and repeating it all over again the next day! We’re a very hydrated family to say the least…don’t even get me started on the cantaloupes.. wow…insane.. there’s so many melon recipes out there on top of it all…so many ideas!! So many good watermelon ideas!! I can’t wait. Stay tuned for the watermelon Gazpacho recipe (last slide) tomorrow on my YouTube channel. It’s just the beginning. 🍉🍈

#LaBreaPartner - Caramelized Bread Pudding & Pumpkin Spiced Ice Cream is on the menu thanks to @labreabakery! My relationship with @labreanakery is decades old and I’ve always loved working with them as a bread vendor in various La restaurants and now as an online chef. This recipe is great if you have any leftover fall pumpkins lingering around and really hits the cozy dessert vibe after a bustling holiday dinner. Hope you enjoy the recipe and shoot me a comment if you end up trying it out or have another version you’d like to see me whip up!
@krogerco 

Ingredients: 
-Caramelized Bread Pudding
1/2 loaf @labreabakery French Baguette (diced)
2 whole eggs 
1 cup sugar 
1 cup milk
4oz butter 
1 tsp ground cinnamon 
1 tsp ground clove 
1/2 cup sweetened steamed pumpkin (large dice)

-Pumpkin Spiced Ice Cream
2 cups heavy cream 
2 cups diced pumpkin 
3/4 cup sugar 
1 tsp ground cinnamon 
1 tsp ground cloves 
1tsp turmeric (optional color)

Lamb Porterhouse (Lamb Loin Chops) & Potato Stacks are on the menu thanks to @superiorfarms! 

This is such a great change of pace from the normal turkey dinner. @SuperiorFarms American lamb loin chops were a pleasure to cook with and I loved the potato/curry cream pairing. The only thing missing here is a spicy cucumber and cabbage salad, torn bread, and a cold beverage. 👌 😋 🥩 🧈 🧄 🌿 🥔 

Full Recipe ⬇️ 
-@SuperiorFarms Pan-Roasted Porterhouse 
Pre-heat a large saute pan on medium-high heat for 2-3 minutes then season the @superiorfarms lamb loin chops with a generous amount of salt and fresh cracked black pepper. 

Add a splash of oil to the pan and sear off both sides of the lamb porterhouse until you have a really good crust. 2-3 minutes on each side including the fat sides. Bast the lamb with butter, crushed garlic, thyme, and rosemary for 1 minutes then allow it to rest off of the heat. Done. 

-Vadouvan Curry Sour Cream 
In a small mixing bowl mix together the sour cream, lemon zest, sumac, and vadouvan dried curry. Done. 

-Potato Stacks 
Sheet or thinly slice the russet potatoes (Yukon works too) and stack them about 1 1/2 inches thick. Cut them into squares or punch out circles then fry them off in 400f frying oil for 3 minutes until a light golden color. Remove them from the oil and onto a paper towel. After about 10 minutes, return the par-fried potatoes back to the frying oil and cook until a dark golden brown. Transfer them to a paper towel and finish with a little salt. Done 

4-5 @superiorfarms lamb loin chops
2 cloves garlic 
Fresh Rosemary and thyme
3 tbsp butter 
4-5 russet potatoes 
3 tbsp sour cream 
1 tsp lemon zest
1 tbsp sumac
1 tbsp vadouvan curry (dried)
Salt and pepper to taste
